Cp%3EAccording%20to%20prosecutors%2C%20the%20scheme%20began%20sometime%20in%202020%20and%20used%20the%20stolen%20identities%20of%20about%2060%20US%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20it%20impacted%20more%20than%20300%20companies%20and%20generated%20more%20than%20%246.8%20million%20in%20revenue%2C%20which%20was%20sent%20back%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-hooked-on-song-praising-north-koreas-dictator-kim-jong-un-report-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENorth%20Korea.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20charging%20document%2C%20prosecutors%20allege%20that%20Chapman%20facilitated%20overseas%20IT%20workers%20posing%20as%20Americans%20using%20the%20stolen%20or%20borrowed%20identities%20of%20US%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChapman%20was%20first%20approached%20in%20March%202020%20by%20an%20unknown%20individual%20asking%20her%20if%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20the%20%26quot%3BUS%20face%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20company%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdd80b675424c132b90b3-e48385e382d2e5d17821a5e1d8e4c86b.ssl.cf1.rackcdn.com%2Fexternal%2Fdcdc-24220-indictment-may82024-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20unsealed%20indictment%20against%20Chapman%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20three%20North%20Korean%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20prosecutors%2C%20the%20scheme%20saw%20overseas%20workers%20apply%20for%20remote%20jobs%20at%20well-known%20US%20companies%2C%20including%20Fortune%20500%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20included%20a%20major%20television%20network%2C%20a%20leading%20Silicon%20Valley%20tech%20company%2C%20an%20aerospace%20manufacturer%2C%20and%20an%20American%20carmaker%2C%20the%20indictment%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20indictment%2C%20the%20workers%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-my-ip%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIP%20addresses%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20it%20appear%20that%20they%20were%20operating%20from%20Chapman's%20house%20and%20within%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20said%20that%20Chapman%20received%20and%20forged%20payroll%20checks%20and%20that%20the%20wages%20of%20the%20foreign%20workers%20were%20paid%20into%20her%20bank%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20added%20that%20much%20of%20the%20income%2C%20though%20to%20be%20at%20least%20%246.8%20million%2C%20was%20falsely%20reported%20to%20the%20IRS%20and%20Social%20Security%20Administration%20under%20the%20names%20of%20US%20citizens%20whose%20identities%20were%20stolen%20or%20borrowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20exchange%2C%20prosecutors%20said%20in%20the%20indictment%20that%20Chapman%20charged%20the%20workers%20monthly%20fees%20for%20her%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attorney%20for%20Chapman%20was%20not%20listed%20in%20court%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20criminal%20complaint%2C%20unsealed%20on%20Thursday%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20man%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fpr%2Fcharges-and-seizures-brought-fraud-scheme-aimed-denying-revenue-workers-associated-north%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOleksandr%20Didenko%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20also%20accused%20of%20operating%20%26quot%3Blaptop%20farms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20press%20release%2C%20Nicole%20M.%20Argentieri%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20Criminal%20Division%2C%20said%20that%20these%20charges%20should%20serve%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bwake-up%20call%26quot%3B%20for%20American%20companies%20employing%20remote%20IT%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20the%20US%20passed%20the%20North%20Korea%20Sanctions%20and%20Policy%20Enhancement%20Act%2C%20which%20aimed%20to%20improve%20the%20enforcement%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-gifted-kim-jong-un-limousine-ignores-un-sanctions-russia-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esanctions%20against%20North%20Korea.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20cut%20North%20Korea%20from%20the%20US%20financial%20system%2C%20which%20led%20to%20various%20schemes%20to%20try%20to%20circumvent%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20assistant%20director%20of%20the%20FBI's%20Counterintelligence%20Division%2C%20Kevin%20Vorndran%2C%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release%20that%20although%20the%20allegations%20may%20seem%20like%20%26quot%3Btypical%20white-collar%26quot%3B%20crime%2C%20they%20represent%20a%20broader%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20described%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bnew%20high-tech%20campaign%20to%20evade%20US%20sanctions%2C%20victimize%20US%20businesses%2C%20and%20steal%20US%20identities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-helped-north-korea-find-remote-jobs-in-us-prosecutors-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715945502000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6647304b14fb5b23cc5d8905%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-helped-north-korea-find-remote-jobs-in-us-prosecutors-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20Arizona%20woman%20aided%20North%20Koreans%20in%20find%20remote-work%20US%20jobs%2C%20funnelling%20their%20wages%20back%20to%20them%20in%20violation%20of%20US%20sanctions%2C%20prosecutors%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzitser%40businessinsider.com%20(Joshua%20Zitser)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-helped-north-korea-find-remote-jobs-in-us-prosecutors-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CI%20try%20not%20to%20think%20about%E2%80%A6OpenAI%20and%20Google%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20ChatGPT-maker%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715945399000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110209633%2Cimgsize-20544.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fi-try-not-to-think-aboutopenai-and-google-says-chatgpt-maker-ceo-sam-altman%2Farticleshow%2F110209672.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20critiqued%20Google's%20event%20aesthetic%2C%20sparking%20controversy.%20OpenAI%20introduced%20GPT-4o%2C%20processing%20audio%2C%20visual%2C%20and%20text%20data.%20Google%20unveiled%20Project%20Astra%20and%20Google%20Search%20updates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20a%20white-collar%20recession%20where%20%24100%2C000%20jobs%20are%20hard%20to%20find%2C%20women%20are%20winning%20out%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22diverse%20group%20of%20women%20conversing%20with%20each%20other%20while%20seated%20at%20a%20table%2C%20with%20a%20red%20and%20blue%20overlay%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F632e17ff78dab80018ed6614%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EKlaus%20Vedfelt%20%2FGetty%3B%20Marianne%20Ayala%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20is%20in%20a%20white-collar%20recession%20with%20new%20%24100%2C000%20job%20openings%20being%20the%20lowest%20since%202014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EData%20shows%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20land%20these%20coveted%20roles%2C%20even%20if%20they%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20apply.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20say%20this%20could%20be%20a%20sign%20of%20DEI%20efforts%20balancing%20the%20gender%20disparity%20in%20senior%20roles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20women%20are%20less%20likely%20than%20their%20male%20peers%20to%20apply%20for%20six-figure%20jobs%2C%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20hired%20for%20high-paying%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icims.com%2Fcompany%2Fnewsroom%2Fmarchinsights2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20global%20recruiting%20software%20firm%20iCIMS.%20In%20an%20analysis%20of%20roughly%20550%20million%20applications%2C%20shared%20exclusively%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20the%20company%20found%20that%20the%20pattern%20goes%20back%20at%20least%20as%20far%20as%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227cb52b98-6fb5-4052-ae14-d593f8d00537%5C%22%3EFewer%20women%20apply%20for%206-figure%20positions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20iCIMS's%20analysis%2C%20women%20have%20made%20up%2041%25%20to%2044%25%20of%20applicants%20for%20six-figure%20jobs%20across%20Asia%2C%20Europe%2C%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20South%20America%2C%20and%20the%20US%20since%202020.%20However%2C%20they%20represent%20between%2049%25%20and%2052%25%20of%20hires%20for%20those%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20though%20they%20constitute%20less%20than%20half%20of%20applications%20for%20six-figure%20jobs%2C%20they%20are%20often%20hired%20for%20more%20than%20half%20of%20those%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222424%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Graph%20showing%20global%20applications%20for%20six-figure%20salary%20jobs%20split%20by%20gender.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6645cbd59fc063e829b19275%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221328%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGraph%20showing%20global%20applications%20for%20six-figure%20salary%20jobs%20split%20by%20gender.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20iCIMS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20fewer%20people%20are%20getting%20hired%20for%20six-figure%20roles.%20Despite%20the%20lowest%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20decades%2C%20hiring%20rates%20for%20high-earners%20have%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-recession-high-salary-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20dropped%20significantly%20since%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%20lower-paying%20roles%2C%20according%20to%20recently%20published%20data%20by%20Vanguard.%20This%20has%20been%20dubbed%20a%20white-collar%20recession.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222432%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Graph%20showing%20global%20hires%20for%20%24100%2C000%20jobs%20split%20by%20gender.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6645cc3a20abc1efe8fa516c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221290%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGraph%20showing%20global%20hires%20for%20%24100%2C000%20jobs%20split%20by%20gender.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20iCIMS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20several%20reasons%20women%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20apply%20for%20these%20increasingly%20rare%20high-paying%20roles%2C%20but%20more%20likely%20to%20get%20them%20once%20they%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2014%2F08%2Fwhy-women-dont-apply-for-jobs-unless-theyre-100-qualified%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAn%20internal%20study%20from%20Hewlett%20Packard%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202014%20indicated%20that%20while%20most%20men%20will%20apply%20for%20a%20job%20if%20they%20meet%20just%2060%25%20of%20the%20requirements%20listed%2C%20most%20women%20will%20apply%20only%20if%20they%20believe%20they%20meet%20all%20of%20them.%20This%20helps%20explain%20why%20fewer%20women%20apply%20but%20also%20hints%20at%20why%20female%20candidates%20are%20more%20successful%3A%20If%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20rule%20themselves%20out%2C%20those%20who%20will%20apply%20will%20be%20higher-quality%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJemimah%20Njuki%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20the%20women's%20economic%20empowerment%20program%20at%20UN%20Women%2C%20told%20BI%20she's%20not%20surprised%20by%20the%20figures%20found%20by%20iCIMS%20analysts.%20She%20believes%20it%20could%20be%20a%20result%20of%20the%20way%20men%20and%20women%20apply%20for%20jobs%20differently%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20women%20are%20less%20likely%20than%20men%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20job%20when%20they%20feel%20that%20they%20don't%20meet%20all%20the%20listed%20requirements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20the%20women%20applying%20for%20high-paying%20roles%20are%20likely%20more%20qualified%20than%20their%20male%20competition%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20have%20a%20higher%20chance%20of%20landing%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d1dd5e1-c654-4b4d-880c-978111bdd6fd%5C%22%3EHigher%20rates%20of%20successful%20female%20applicants%20signal%20that%20DEI%20is%20working%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20also%20indicate%20that%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20initiatives%20are%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYana%20Rodgers%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Women%20and%20Work%20at%20Rutgers%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20considers%20it%20a%20supply%20and%20demand%20issue.%20Female%20applicants%20for%20high-paying%20jobs%20are%20in%20short%20supply%20because%20they%20self-select%20out%20of%20applying%2C%20while%20employers%20are%20actively%20trying%20to%20hire%20women%20for%20powerful%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20why%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20hired%20over%20men%20in%20six-figure%20roles%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20it's%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20initiatives%20at%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rodgers.%20The%20director%20also%20polled%20her%20peers%20at%20the%20university.%20They%20agreed%3A%20the%20data%20could%20indicate%20that%20efforts%20to%20correct%20gaps%20in%20gender%20representation%20at%20the%20top%20of%20businesses%20are%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENjuki%20feels%20the%20same%20way.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20companies%2C%20because%20of%20historical%20imbalances%20in%20the%20gender%20composition%20of%20senior%20management%20teams%2C%20are%20aiming%20to%20increase%20those%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20companies%20would%20be%20looking%20for%20more%20female%20talent%20to%20fill%20those%20higher%20positions%20because%20they%20are%20currently%20underrepresented.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20United%20States%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-diversity-departments-some-ceos-talk-committed-racial-justice-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDEI%20professionals%20have%20been%20early%20victims%20of%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20some%20employers%20have%20been%20putting%20the%20brakes%20on%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20initiatives%20after%20public%20and%20legal%20challenges%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F12%2F27%2Fdei-affirmative-action-legal-challenges-corporate-america%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20and%20organizations%20who%20consider%20DEI%20practices%20to%20be%20a%20form%20of%20discrimination%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20plenty%20of%20companies%20have%20not%20abandoned%20their%20equity%20plans.%20In%20January%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firp.cdn-website.com%2F0dd693a6%2Ffiles%2Fuploaded%2FBriefing%2520-%2520Senior%2520Executives%2520on%2520Diversity%2520Initiatives%2520vEXTERNAL.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMorning%20Consult%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20more%20than%2080%25%20of%20executives%20say%20DEI%20is%20critical%20to%20their%20business%20strategies%2C%20and%20more%20than%2060%25%20say%20they%20anticipate%20such%20strategies%20only%20becoming%20more%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0820e9b-c90d-46a1-88c7-0303ec1540e5%5C%22%3EBeware%20of%20the%20'glass%20cliff'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20women%20hired%20into%20high-ranking%20roles%20may%20find%20it%20untenable%20to%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20sometimes%20stack%20the%20odds%20against%20them%20before%20they%20even%20start%20the%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Njuki%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-and-people-of-color-face-glass-cliff-us-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglass%20cliff.%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20The%20term%20was%20coined%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F343178704_The_who_when_and_why_of_the_glass_cliff_phenomenon_A_meta-analysis_of_appointments_to_precarious_leadership_positions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20who%20studied%20the%20phenomenon%3C%2Fa%3E%20whereby%20a%20person%20from%20an%20underrepresented%20background%20is%20promoted%20to%20a%20senior%20leadership%20position%20during%20a%20difficult%20time%20for%20a%20company%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20failure%20is%20high.%20It%20disproportionately%20impacts%20women.%20They%20are%20put%20in%20leadership%20roles%20when%20a%20company%20is%20in%20decline%2C%20which%20provides%20a%20justification%20when%20they%20are%20asked%20to%20leave%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENjuki%20added%20that%20while%20hiring%20women%20is%20important%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20even%20more%20important%20that%20they%20be%20hired%20in%20companies%20that%20are%20doing%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Ffeatured-insights%2Fdiversity-and-inclusion%2Fwomen-in-the-workplace%23%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20Women%20in%20the%20Workplace%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20McKinsey%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FLeanIn.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELeanIn.org%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20gender%20representation%20in%20leadership%20remains%20imbalanced.%20Men%20hold%20roughly%2052%25%20of%20entry-level%20positions%2C%20and%20women%20about%2047%25.%20At%20the%20senior%20manager%20level%2C%20men%20constitute%2060%25%20of%20the%20workforce%2C%20while%20women%20make%20up%2033%25.%20With%20each%20jump%20in%20rank%2C%20the%20gap%20grows.%20Only%2028%25%20of%20executives%20are%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eace2286-4c56-4d1e-b0c8-508fc547779a%5C%22%3EMore%20women%20in%206-figure%20jobs%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20the%20pay%20gap%20is%20closing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20equal%20representation%20in%20leadership%20may%20lag%2C%20could%20the%20data%20from%20iCIMS%20signal%20a%20change%20in%20the%20gender%20pay%20gap%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20six-figure%20salary%20doesn't%20mean%20a%20woman%20is%20paid%20equitably%20against%20her%20male%20peers.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20they%20are%20applying%20for%20these%20six-figure%20jobs%20does%20not%20imply%20that%20the%20gender%20pay%20gap%20is%20narrowing%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Njuki.%20%26quot%3BThis%20would%20require%20a%20comparison%20between%20the%20women%20in%20those%20six-figure%20jobs%20and%20the%20men%20in%20those%20six-figure%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERodgers%20is%20hopeful%20and%20believes%20the%20trend%20is%20a%20positive%20signal.%20%26quot%3BA%20big%20reason%20for%20the%20gender%20pay%20gap%20is%20not%20enough%20women%20in%20the%20higher-paid%20managerial%20and%20leadership%20positions.%20It's%20not%20going%20to%20eliminate%20the%20pay%20gap%2C%20but%20it%20should%20help%20to%20close%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-women-winning-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715944974000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F632e17ff78dab80018ed6611%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-women-winning-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fewer%20people%20are%20being%20hired%20for%20%24100k%20jobs.%20While%20women%20are%20less%20likely%20than%20men%20to%20apply%2C%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20hired%20for%20high-paying%20roles.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22emilymccrary%40gmail.com%20(Emily%20McCrary-Ruiz-Esparza%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-c