two%20years%20ago%2C%20have%20moved%20up%20the%20ranks%20in%20the%202024%20edition%20released%20on%20Friday%20thanks%20to%20the%20Akshata%20Murty's%20lucrative%20Infosys%20shareholding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%2C%20both%2044%2C%20have%20risen%20from%20275th%20last%20year%20to%20245th%20with%20an%20estimated%20wealth%20of%20GBP%20651%20million%2C%20making%20them%20the%20%26quot%3Bwealthiest%20people%20to%20call%2010%20Downing%20Street%20home%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkshata%20Murty's%20earnings%20are%20said%20to%20far%20exceed%20that%20of%20her%20husband%20as%20financial%20statements%20published%20in%20February%20are%20quoted%20to%20say%20Rishi%20Sunak%20made%20GBP%202.2%20million%20in%202022-23%20compared%20to%20AkshataMurty's%20estimated%20GBP%2013%20million%20in%20dividends%20over%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20couple's%20most%20valued%20asset%20is%20Akshata%20Murty's%20shareholding%20in%20Infosys%2C%20a%20Bangalore-based%20IT%20company%20co-founded%20by%20Akshata%20Murty's%20father%20%5BNarayan%20Murthy%5D%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20the%20newspaper's%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20shares%20have%20grown%20in%20value%20by%20GBP%20108.8%20million%20to%20nearly%20GBP%20590%20million.%20The%20latest%20annual%20report%20suggests%20that%20Murty%20received%20about%20GBP%2013%20million%20in%20dividends%20during%20that%20time%20-%20adding%20to%20the%20more%20than%20a%20million%20pounds%20she%20has%20been%20paid%20in%20previous%20years.%20She%20is%20poised%20to%20receive%20another%20GBP%2010.5%20million%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20annual%20compilation%20of%20Britain's%20wealthiest%20families%20is%20once%20again%20topped%20by%20the%20Indian-origin%20Hinduja%20family%2C%20who%20saw%20their%20wealth%20increase%20over%20the%20past%20year%20to%20hit%20GBP%2037.196%20billion%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20opening%20of%20their%20brand-new%20luxury%20OWO%20Hotel%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UK-based%20family's%20group%20of%20companies%2C%20headed%20by%20chairman%20G.P.%20Hinduja%2C%20operates%20in%2048%20countries%20and%20across%20several%20sectors%20-%20automotive%2C%20oil%20and%20speciality%20chemicals%2C%20banking%20and%20finance%2C%20IT%2C%20cyber%20security%2C%20healthcare%2C%20trading%2C%20infrastructure%20project%20development%2C%20media%20and%20entertainment%2C%20power%2C%20and%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20been%20a%20year%20of%20expansion%20through%20acquisition%20for%20the%20group%2C%20made%20possible%20in%20part%20by%20growing%20stock%20market%20valuations%20of%20the%20family's%20main%20listed%20holdings%2C%20which%20have%20risen%20to%20a%20total%20of%20GBP%208.7%20billion%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20the%20newspaper's%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%2010%20of%20the%202024%20'Sunday%20Times%20Rich%20List'%20sees%20another%20set%20of%20India-born%20brothers%2C%20David%20and%20Simon%20Reuben%2C%20build%20on%20their%20wealth%20to%20rise%20to%20third%20place%20from%20last%20year's%20fourth%2C%20with%20a%20fortune%20estimated%20at%20around%20GBP%2024.977%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20No.%208%20is%20NRI%20tycoon%20of%20ArcelorMittal%20steelworks%20Lakshmi%20N.%20Mittal%2C%20who%20slips%20two%20places%20from%20last%20year%20with%20an%20estimated%20GBP%2014.921%20billion%2C%20followed%20by%20Vedanta%20Resources'%20industrialist%20Anil%20Agarwal%20at%20No.%2023%20with%20an%20estimated%20GBP%207%20billion%20-%20down%20one%20rank%20from%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20Indian-origin%20billionaires%20on%20the%202024%20list%20include%20textiles%20entrepreneur%20Prakash%20Lohia%20at%20No.%2030%20with%20an%20estimated%20GBP%206.23%20billion%3B%20retail%20majors%20Mohsin%20and%20Zuber%20Issa%20at%20No.%2039%20with%20GBP%205%20billion%3B%20and%20pharma%20chiefs%20Navin%20and%20Varsha%20Engineer%20at%2058%20with%20GBP%203%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong